    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_AddReportUsageLog",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to log the usage of reports within a system. It records details about the report being accessed, the stored procedure associated with it, the user requesting the report, and various billing period parameters. This information is inserted into the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ReportUsageLog",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table within the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Audit",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema, providing an audit trail of report usage."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving basic SQL operations such as variable assignment, conditional logic, and an "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "INSERT",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " statement. It does not involve complex logic, loops, or error handling, making it relatively simple to understand and maintain."
        }
      ]
    },
